[[!meta title="Accessibility"]]

Tails uses the <span class="application">GNOME Desktop</span> that
provides many accessibility features as documented in the [GNOME Access
Guide](http://library.gnome.org/users/gnome-access-guide/2.32/gnome-access-guide.html).
For a summary of those features, read the [quick
reference](http://library.gnome.org/users/gnome-access-guide/2.32/gnome-access-guide.html#quickref)
section of this guide.

If you **prefer a pointing device over the keyboard**, Tails includes
the [[<span class="application">Florence</span> virtual
keyboard|first_steps/introduction_to_gnome_and_the_tails_desktop#florence]],
instead of the <span class="application">GNOME On-Screen
Keyboard</span>.

If you want to **have the screen magnified**, you can use either of the
following tools:

  - [<span class="application">Orca</span> as a screen
    magnifier](http://library.gnome.org/users/gnome-access-guide/2.32/gnome-access-guide.html#ats-2).
  - The command-line tool [<span class="application">GNOME
    Magnifier</span>](http://linux.die.net/man/1/magnifier).
